<h2><img src="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/images/wrd.gif" align=left hspace=0 width=100 height=100>Wildlife ResourcesDivision</h2>
<p>&#160;The Wildlife Resources Division manages, protects, and encourages the wise use of all wildlife, fish and 
protected plants. The division operates recreation areas for hunting, fishing, and other wildlife-related 
recreation, and enforces laws regulating wildlife, boating and littering to ensure the protection of Georgia&#146;s 
natural resources. Through ongoing information and education programs, the division promotes conservation, sportsmanship, 
safety awareness, and encourages citizens to be responsible stewards of the environment.<br>
</p>
<hr>
<p>David Waller, Director<br>
DNR-- Wildlife Resources Division<br>
2070 U.S. Hwy. 278, S.E. Click HERE to read a message from the director<br>
Social Circle, GA 30279<br>
(770) 918-6400<br>
<br>
More about the Wildlife Resources Division<br>
Mission Statement<br>
Wildlife and Fisheries Facts -- Facts, figures and other &quot;gee whiz&quot; information<br>
Turn In Poachers -- How to report poaching, fish kills, and other wildlife-related violations<br>
<a href="Fishmgmt/index.htm">Fisheries Management</a> -- Freshwater fishing opportunities, regulations, licenses, aquatic education, other angling-related 
information<br>
<a href="Gamemgmt/index.htm">Game Management</a> --Hunting opportunities, regulations and wildlife management areas<br>
<a href="Le/index.htm">Law Enforcement</a> -- Hunter Education Program, boating safety and education programs, and other enforcement information <br>
<a href="Nongame/index.htm">Nongame Program</a> -- Watchable wildlife, endangered species, and other information<br>
<a href="Gnhp/index.htm">Natural Heritage Program</a> -- Wetlands, protected plants, and natural areas in Georgia<br>
<a href="Boatreg/index.htm">Licensing and Boat Registration</a> --How to purchase hunting or fishing licenses, register a boat, or get a replacement license<br>
News Releases -- Current news releases distributed by the Wildlife Resources Division<br>
Careers -- Information on careers with the Wildlife Resources Division<br>
Commonly Asked Questions -- Answers to commonly asked questions<br>
Wildlife Education and Outreach -- wildlife and aquatic outreach and education programs<br>
Documents for Public Comment -- View Wildlife Resources Division documents out for public comment<br>
</p>
