<body background="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/images/whttxtr1.jpg" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p>[ <a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/index.htm">Home</a> | <a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/news.htm">What's New</a> | <a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/toc.htm">TOC</a> | <a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/feedback.htm">Feedback</a> | <a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/search.htm">Search</a> ]</p>
<h2><img src="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/images/wrd.gif" align=left hspace=0 width=100 height=100>Law Enforcement Home Page</h2>
<p>The Law Enforcement Section is responsible for protecting Georgia&#146;s wildlife populations by enforcing laws, 
rules and regulations pertaining to game and nongame animals, threatened and endangered plants and animals, 
exotic animals, boating safety, litter and waste control and other natural resource issues. The section also 
administers the state&#146;s hunter education and boating safety programs. Conservation rangers investigate violations of wildlife 
laws, as well as hunting and boating accidents. They also conduct classes and programs to educate citizens about wildlife laws 
and safety practices.</p>
<hr>
<p>Col. V.J. Garrison, Chief<br>
DNR-- Wildlife Resources Division<br>
