<h3><a name="recycle">Recycling, Waste Exchange, and &quot;Green
Design&quot; Resources</a></h3>
<p><a href="http://www.grn.com">The Global Recycling Network</a>
(http://www.grn.com) This site provides a reference library,
recycling directories, industry newsletters and books, trade
associations, funding and grant sources, current prices for
recyclables, recycling stock market watch and a virtual
marketplace.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.msn.fullfeed.com/wastesort">&quot;Wastesort&quot;
software</a> (http://www.msn.fullfeed.com/wastesort) The trial
version is available and is provided by Recycler's World.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.tsdcentral.com">TSD Central</a>
(http://www.tsdcentral.com) This is a commercial site that runs
an industrial waste exchange based on a RCRA waste
characterization.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.sentex.net/recycle/">Recycler's World</a>
(http://www.sentex.net/recycle) This is a trading site that also
supplies information relating to secondary or recyclable
commodities, by products, used and surplus items, and collectible
items.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.earthcycle.com/g/p/earthcycle/">The
National Materials Exchange Network</a>
(http://www.earthcycle.com/g/p/earthcycle) is an online
marketplace linking 42 material exchanges in North America. It is
a multi-user bulletin board with a database and e-mail.</p>
<p><a href="http://w3.pnl.gov:2080/esp/greenguide/">Pacific
Northwest Laboratories</a>
(http://w3.pnl.gov:2080/esp/greenguide/) provides information on
purchasing recycled products, recycling, and affirmative
procurement.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.isd.net/cpm/">Recycling Insights</a>
(http://www.isd.net/cpm/) provides solid waste
management/recycling software.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.noraoil.com/where.html">National Oil
Recycler's Association (NORA) State Contacts for Used Oil</a>
(http://www.noraoil.com/where.html) This site includes basic
instructions for disposal of used oil as well as state contacts
on used oil in the United States. </p>
<p><a href="http://euler.berkeley.edu/green/cgdm.html">The Center
for Green Design and Manufacturing</a>
(http://euler.berkeley.edu/green/cgdm.html) The site, located at
the University of California at Berkeley, includes hierarchical
decision strategies for &quot;green&quot; practices,
process-based approaches, and environmental impact assessment.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.ebuild.com/">Environmental Building News
(EBN)</a> (http://www.ebuild.com/) is a newsletter on
environmentally sustainable design and construction. EBN is
comprised of articles, reviews, and news stories and is a prime
resource on energy-efficient, resource-efficient, and healthy
building practices. The Newsletter addresses material selection,
siting, indoor air quality, daylighting, and more. The web site
provides a back issues section to create a collection of
information on green buildings, products, and technologies. The
&quot;Hot News&quot; section includes current information. A
summary is provided of the current issue and a calendar offers
future activities and events in the green building world. </p>
<p>Pacific Northwest Laboratories provides the <a
href="http://w3.pnl.gov:2080/DFE/home.html">Pollution Prevention
by Design Home Page</a> (http://w3.pnl.gov:2080/DFE/home.html).
This site will soon have a downloadable version of P<sup>2</sup>-EDGE
software (Pollution Prevention Environmental Design Guide for
Engineers) available for DOE employees and contractors.</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<hr>
<h3><a name="tech">Technical Associations and Societies and
Commercial Sites</a></h3>
<p><a href="http://es.inel.gov/aipp/">American Institute for
Pollution Prevention</a> (http://es.inel.gov/aipp) This is a
nonprofit organization comprised of industry trade associations
and professional societies.</p>
<p><a href="http://es.inel.gov/nppr">National Pollution
Prevention Roundtable</a> (http://es.inel.gov/nppr)</p>
<p><a href="http://www.geopac.com">Environmental Professional's
Guide to the Internet</a> (http://www.geopac.com)</p>
<p><a href="http://www.finishing.com/">The Home Page of the
Finishing Industry</a> (http://www.finishing.com) includes
information from AESF (The American Electroplaters and Surface
Finishers' Society, Inc.</p>
<p><a href="http://cai.eclipse.net/home2.htm">National Metal
Finishing Resource Center</a> (http://cai.eclipse.net/home2.htm)
is being designed to be the most substantial, comprehensive,
environmental compliance, technical assistance and pollution
prevention information source available for the Metal Finishing
industry. The Resource Center is specifically targeted for the
metal finishing industry and technical assistance providers.
Currently, a password is required but the application and receipt
are well explained. </p>
<p><a href="http://www.ssawma.org/index.htm">The Southern Section
of the Air &amp; Waste Management Association</a>
(http://www.ssawma.org/index.htm) provides up-to-date information
about their activities for members in GA, AL, TN, and MS.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.awma.org/">The Air &amp; Waste Management
Association</a> (http://www.awma.org) provides listings of
publications, membership information, meeting dates, and
employment resources.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.plasticsresource.com">American Plastics
Council</a> (http://www.plasticsresource.com)</p>
<p><a href="http://www.ansi.org/">The American National Standards
Institute (ANSI)</a> (http://www.ansi.org)</p>
<p><a href="http://www.amweld.org/">American Welding Society</a>
(http://www.amweld.org)</p>
<p><a href="http://www.gnet.org">The Global Network for
Environmental Technology (GNET)</a> (http://www.gnet.org)</p>
<p><a href="http://www.iso.ch/">ISO</a> (http://www.iso.ch) Find
out the latest about ISO 9000 and ISO 14000.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.envirobiz.com/">Environmental Information
(EI)</a> (http://www.envirobiz.com)</p>
<p><a href="http://www.iti.org/ee/eem">ITI Energy and Environment
Center</a> (http://www.iti.org/ee/eem) This site includes
numerous links useful to manufacturers.</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<hr>
<h3><a name="federal">Federal Government Sites</a></h3>
<p>Telnet to the <a href="telnet://locis.loc.gov/">Library of
Congress</a> (telnet://locis.loc.gov). Search for topics online
by author, book, subject, etc.</p>
<p>Telnet to the <a href="telnet://ttnbbs.rtpnc.epa.gov/">Research
Triangle Park Air BBS</a> (telnet://ttnbbs.rtpnc.epa.gov). There
is a wealth of information here for professionals in the air
monitoring and air pollution control areas.</p>
<p><i>Note that your web browser must be setup with a default
telnet application for the telnet links to work properly.</i></p>
<p><a href="http://www.fedworld.gov/">Fedworld</a>
(http://www.fedworld.gov) is a gateway to 125 federal bulletin
boards.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.pls.com:8001/his/cfr.html">The Code of
Federal Regulations</a> (http://www.pls.com:8001/his/cfr.html) </p>
<p><a href="http://www.nttc.edu/environmental.html">National
Technology Transfer Center's Environmental Technology Gateway</a>
(http://www.nttc.edu/environmental.html)</p>
<p><a href="http://h2o.usgs.gov/">U.S. Geological Survey Water
Resources Information</a> (http://h2o.usgs.gov)</p>
<p><a href="http://thomas.loc.gov/">THOMAS</a>
(http://thomas.loc.gov) contains full text of current
Congressional legislation.</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<hr>
<h3><a name="ehs">Environment, Health, and Safety</a></h3>
<p><a href="gopher://gopher.chem.utah.edu/11/msds">MSDS On-line</a>
(gopher://gopher.chem.utah.edu/11/msds)</p>
<p><a href="http://www.enviro-net.com/">Enviro-net</a>
(http://www.enviro-net.com) is a site produced by the publishers
of Georgia Environmental News.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.wateronline.com">Water Online</a>
(http://www.wateronline.com)</p>
<p><a href="http://www,groundwater.com/">Water-Geology-Environmental
Information</a> (http://www.groundwater.com/) This site offers
several on-line resources relating to groundwater. The directory
of listservers contains a list of nearly 100 environmental,
geology, and hydrology mailing lists; the products and services
directory contains contact information for companies offering
products and services relating to the groundwater field; and the
links area contains links to groundwater environmental and
geology web sites. </p>
<p><a href="http://tamora.acsiom.org/info/envirotext/">EnviroText</a>
(http://tamora.cs.umass.edu/info/envirotext/ ) is an online
library consisting primarily of environment, safety, and health
requirements. EnviroText contains the following datasets: the
entire United States Code; most of the Code of Federal
Regulations and the Federal Register, which is updated daily;
Presidential Executive Orders from 1945 to the present; most
Indian Tribal Codes; a complete set of Indian Tribal Agreements
and Treaties; and a set of all International Agreements and
Treaties. </p>
<p><a href="http://db.nihs.go.jp/genera/KEMI/">Swedish National
Chemicals Inspectorate Sunset Project</a>
(http://db.nihs.go.jp/genera/KEMI/) The Sunset Project has
collected lists of chemical substances originating from
authorities and other national or international bodies in an
attempt to broadly cover relatively well known substances that
have been given attention because of their harmful properties to
human health and the environment. The site offers a chemical
substances search as well as lists divided by topic including:
environmental hazards, health hazards, combined environmental and
health hazards, and exposure. </p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<hr>
<h3><a name="Energy ">Energy Related Sites</a></h3>
<p><a href="http://www.epri.com/">The Electric Power Research
Institute (EPRI)</a> (http://www.epri.com) provides research and
development activities for the electric utility industry
including P<sup>2</sup> initiatives.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.eia.doe.gov/">Energy Information
Administration</a> (http://www.eia.doe.gov) has several
publications available online.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.epa.gov/docs/GCDOAR/EnergyStar.html">Energy
Star Programs</a>
(http://www.epa.gov/docs/GCDOAR/EnergyStar.html)</p>
<p><a href="http://www.weea.org/">World Energy Efficiency
Association (WEEA)</a> (http://www.weea.org/) site includes News
and Updates, WEEA Institutional Information, and listings of
electronically available WEEA documents and information. Of
interest is the International Directory of Energy Efficiency
Institutions, WEEA Energy Efficiency Organizational Profiles, the
Best Practices Program Case Study Series, and the Internet Energy
and Environment Sampler, version 2.0. </p>
<p><a href="http://www.eren.doe.gov">U.S. DOE, Energy Efficiency
and Renewable Energy Network</a> (http://www.eren.doe.gov)
provides information on renewable energy and energy efficient
technology.</p>
<p><a href="http://oipea-www.rutgers.edu">Office of Industrial
Productivity and Energy Assessment</a>
(http://oipea-www.rutgers.edu) contains a database of industry
assessments and recommendations.</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<hr>
<h3><a name="agri">Agricultural Sites</a></h3>
<p><a href="http://www.wisc.edu/farmasyst">National Farm*A*Syst</a>
(http://www.wisc.edu/farmasyst)</p>
<p><a href="http://www.bae.edu/outreach/aware/index.html">Animal
Waste Awareness in Research and Extension (AWARE)</a>
(http://www.bae.uga.edu/outreach/aware/index.html)</p>
<p><a href="http://www.agrialt.com">Agri-Alternatives</a>
(http://www.agrialt.com) has discussion groups on inventions,
precision farming, software and information systems, and
innovation and technology.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.snymor.edu/~drewwe/njc/">Not Just Cows</a>
(http://www.snymor.edu/~drewwe/njc) lists a variety of internet
resources in agriculture including news groups, discussion
groups, electronic journals and magazines, cooperative extension
services, and data files.</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<hr>
<h3><a name="Georgia">Other Georgia Information</a></h3>
<p><a href="http://www.vais.net/~bweiner/states/georgia.htm">Georgia
Online Network</a>
(http://www.vais.net/~bweiner/states/georgia.htm) </p>
<p><a
href="http://www.mindspring.com/~tede/cherokee_ga/recycle.html">Cherokee
County Clean Commission</a>
(http://www.mindspring.com/~tede/cherokee_ga/recycle.html)</p>
<p>Locate other WWW Servers located in <a
href="http://www.emory.edu/GaCern/GA.html">Georgia</a>
(http://www.emory.edu/GaCern/GA.html)</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<hr>
<h3><a name="search">Search for Other Servers</a></h3>
<p>Search for other types of environmental servers using the <a
href="http://ecosys.drdr.virginia.edu/Environment.html">WWW
Virtual Library</a>
(http://ecosys.drdr.virginia.edu/Environment.html)</p>
<p><a href="http://www.webdirectory.com">Yahoo's Amazing
Environmental Organization Web Directory</a>
(http://www.webdirectory.com/)</p>
<p><a
href="http://www.seattle.battelle.org/services/e&amp;s/moresite.htm">Another
Listing of P2 Sites</a>
(http://www.seattle.battelle.org/services/e&amp;s/moresite.htm)
provided by Battelle</p>
<p><a href="http://www.uml.edu/turi/">P2Gems</a>
(http://www.uml.edu/turi/) is a searchable index of P<sup>2</sup>
web sites.</p>
<p>Search the Web for other P<sup>2</sup> Sites Using <a
href="http://www.webcrawler.com/">Webcrawler</a>
(http://www.webcrawler.com)</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
