<title>NICE3 GRANT</title>
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="Gray_Textured.gif">
<h1 align="center"><img
src="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/images/p2ad.gif"
align="absmiddle" width="100" height="100"><font color="#008040">Pollution
Prevention Assistance Division</font></h1>
<h2 align="center">NICE<sup>3</sup> Grants</h2>
<p align="center">[<em>From the Source - </em>Spring 1995]</p>
<hr>
<p>As many of you are aware, P<sup>2</sup>AD currently has two
grants from the Department of Energy's (DOE) National Industrial
Competitiveness through Energy, Environment, and Economics (NICE<sup>3</sup>)
program. One of these projects is investigating the automated
reuse of dyebaths in carpet manufacturing. Shaw Industries in
Dalton will be the demonstration site for this grant. Our other
current project is developing an advanced mineral calcining
process, which will improve lime recovery in the pulp and paper
industry. The next phase of this project will be a
commercial-scale demonstration at the Weyerhaeuser Corporation
plant in Oglethorpe.</p>
<p>The Division's past success in the NICE<sup>3</sup> program
can be attributed in part to our thorough and lengthy review of
all proposals submitted for funding. Additionally, our past
experiences have taught us that a period of several months will
be necessary to produce the final proposal documents for
submission to DOE. Therefore, we strongly recommend that anyone
who wishes to apply for the NICE<sup>3</sup> 1996 program submit
an abstract for P<sup>2</sup>AD's consideration on or before
August 2, 1995. This will enable us to have sufficient time to
work with the projects prior to DOE's two-page abstract deadline
of October 2, 1995. Note that this does not preclude applicants
from working with other eligible state agencies in submitting a
proposal past this recommended deadline ; the August 2 date
applies only if you are seeking to submit an application through
P<sup>2</sup>AD. See the description below for more details.</p>
<h3>NICE<sup>3</sup> Grant Solicitation</h3>
<p>The Georgia Pollution Prevention Assistance Division is
pleased to solicit abstracts from parties with innovative
pollution prevention projects who are interested in applying for
the 1996 round of NICE<sup>3</sup> grants from the Department of
Energy. The timeline for the 1996 Solicitation is as follows:</p>
<ul>
    <li>August 2, 1995 - Recommended submission date for project
        abstract to P<sup>2</sup>AD </li>
    <li>October 2, 1995 - Deadline for submission of two-page
        abstract to DOE</li>
    <li>January 16, 1996 - Deadline for application package
        submission to DOE</li>
    <li>April 22, 1996 - Awards announcement </li>
</ul>
<p>For more information, contact Greg Andrews at (404) 651-5120
or 800-685-2443.</p>
