<h2 align="center"><strong>Entry Level Application Instructions</strong></h2>
<hr>
<h3><strong>How to complete the Entry Level application</strong>.</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Please print or type all information. </li>
    <li>Submit one copy of the completed application. </li>
    <li>Application forms may be photocopied and completed. </li>
    <li>Applications are accepted anytime. </li>
    <li>Applications may be hand delivered, mailed, faxed or
        e-mailed. </li>
    <li>The address is: </li>
</ul>
<dl>
    <dd>Pollution Prevention Assistance Division</dd>
    <dd>Attn: P<sup>3</sup> Program</dd>
    <dd>Suite 450</dd>
    <dd>7 Martin Luther King, Jr. Drive</dd>
    <dd>Atlanta, GA 30334</dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dd>Fax: (404) 651-5130</dd>
    <dd>E-mail: p2ad@ix.netcom.com</dd>
</dl>
<ul>
    <li>You may generate your own form. If so, please follow the
        numbering system on the application.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3><strong>Section 1.0 - General Information</strong></h3>
<p><strong>1.1 Facility name: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.2 Site Address: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.3 Mail Address: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.4 Phone: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.5 Fax: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.6 Contact: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.7 Title: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.8 Phone: </strong>(If different from above)<strong> </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.9 Fax: </strong>(If different from above) </p>
<p><strong>1.10 E-mail: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.11 List SIC codes that apply to your facility or
describes what your facility manufactures: </strong>(If you do
not know which SIC code applies to your facility, then briefly
describe the facility's processes)</p>
<p><strong>1.12 EPA ID number: </strong>(if applicable)</p>
<hr>
<h3><strong>Section 2.0 - Pollution Prevention Plan</strong></h3>
<p>You may attach an existing plan, or use the following form
(Sections 2-4) as your plan. Existing plans must include all of
the elements requested below.</p>
<p><strong>2.1 Provide the facility's written pollution
prevention policy statement that indicates management's and
employees' commitment to preventing pollution and waste at the
source.</strong></p>
<p>This is the facility's statement indicating a commitment by
management and employees to preventing pollution at the source.</p>
<p><strong>2.2 Provide a brief description of the facility's
operations. </strong>(If available, provide a process flow
diagram)</p>
<p>Describe what product(s) is made at the facility and what
processes are used to make the product(s).</p>
<p><strong>2.3 Waste stream identification, facility production
and reduction goals.</strong></p>
<p>The following chart is designed to help establish a baseline
year for measuring reductions. Identify the waste streams that
your facility generates and establish production for the baseline
year. Not all facilities generate waste in each category.
Establish reduction goals, by percentage, for the following year
and for the long-term. The projected year for achieving the
long-term goals must be included.</p>
<p><strong>2.4 Facility waste stream and reduction goals chart.</strong></p>
<p>At top of the table, enter a baseline year (1995 or earlier).
For each type of waste (hazardous, wastewater, air emissions, and
solid waste), enter the following information:</p>
<p><em>Column 1</em> - No entry necessary.</p>
<p><em>Column 2</em> - Enter the source(s) of each type of waste
generated. If no waste of the type listed in column 1 is
generated, enter None and go to next row. Example sources include
painting and cleaning operations, materials past expiration date
for hazardous wastes, potable water or process water for
wastewater sources, boiler or paint booth for air emissions, and
pallets, scrap steel, office paper for solid waste sources. </p>
<p><em>Column 3</em> - Enter the total amount of waste generated
in the baseline year for each category of waste. Use units of
pounds for hazardous waste and air emissions, gallons for
wastewater, and tons for total solid waste.</p>
<p><em>Column 4 </em>- Enter baseline year production in specific
units. Product quantities or dollar values are preferred. Example
units include automobiles, linear feet of pipe, number of
employees, annual sales, gallons of cleaning chemicals. Beyond
the entry level, production numbers will be used to normalize
waste reduction percentages based on production levels.</p>
<p><em>Column 5</em> - For each category of waste, enter your
reduction goal for calendar year 1996 versus your waste
generation in the baseline year. </p>
<p>1996 Reduction goal = (1996 waste generation/Baseline year
waste generation)x 100 (%) </p>
<p><em>Column 6</em> - For each category of waste, enter your
long term reduction goal versus your waste generation in the
baseline year. Also enter the year that you propose achieving
this goal by.</p>
<p>LT Reduction goal = (LT waste generation/Baseline year waste
generation)x 100 (%) </p>
<p>Your long term reduction goal will be used as a metric in
applying for Achievement Level and Model Level Certification in
the Pollution Prevention Partners program. </p>
<p>For each type of waste, enter a short description of potential
methods for minimizing wastes through pollution prevention.</p>
<hr>
<h3><strong>Section 3.0 - Employee Participation</strong></h3>
<p><strong>3.1 Describe the makeup of the facility's pollution
prevention team and how it functions.</strong></p>
<p>List positions or areas of responsibility represented on the
team, how often it meets and to whom the team reports.</p>
<p><strong>3.2 Describe how employees of the facility are
notified of the pollution prevention program.</strong></p>
<p>Indicate by what means employees were notified of the
pollution prevention program.</p>
<p><strong>3.3 Describe how employees are encouraged to
participate in the pollution prevention program.</strong></p>
<p>List any motivational efforts or incentives offered to
employees for contributing to the program.</p>
<hr>
<h3>Section 4.0 - Management Concurrence</h3>
<p><strong>The highest ranking manager at the facility must sign
the following statement:</strong></p>
<p>I certify that the information contained in this document is
true, accurate and complete.</p>
<p>Company Officer:______________________________</p>
<p>Title:______________________________</p>
<p>Date:______________________________</p>
