<body background="Gray_Textured.gif">
<h1 align="center"><img
src="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/images/p2ad.gif"
align="absmiddle" width="100" height="100"><font color="#008040">Pollution
Prevention Assistance Division</font></h1>
<h2 align="center"><b>Achievement Level Application Instructions</b> </h2>
<hr>
<h3><b>How to complete the Achievement Level application.</b> </h3>
<ul>
    <li>Please print or type all information. </li>
    <li>Submit one copy of the completed application. </li>
    <li>Application forms may be photocopied and completed. </li>
    <li>Applications are accepted anytime. </li>
    <li>Applications may be hand delivered, mailed, faxed or
        e-mailed. </li>
    <li>The address is: </li>
</ul>
<dl>
    <dd>Pollution Prevention Assistance Division</dd>
    <dd>Attn: P<sup>3</sup> Program</dd>
    <dd>Suite 450</dd>
    <dd>7 Martin Luther King, Jr. Drive</dd>
    <dd>Atlanta, GA 30334</dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dd>Fax: (404) 651-5130</dd>
    <dd>E-mail: p2ad@ix.netcom.com</dd>
</dl>
<ul>
    <li>You may generate your own form. If so, please follow the
        numbering system on the application.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3><b>Section 1.0 - General Information</b> </h3>
<p><strong>1.1 Facility name: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.2 Site Address: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.3 Mail Address: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.4 Phone: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.5 Fax: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.6 Contact: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.7 Title: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.8 Contact&#146;s Phone: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.9 Contact&#146;s Fax: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.10 Contact&#146;s E-mail: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.11 List Standard Industrial Classification (SIC)
codes that apply to your facility or describe what your facility
manufactures: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1.12 EPA ID number: </strong>(if applicable)</p>
<hr>
<h3><b>Section 2.0</b> - <b>Pollution Prevention Plan</b> </h3>
<p>You may attach an existing plan, or use the following form
(Sections 2-7) as your plan. Existing plans must include all of
the elements requested below. </p>
<p><b>2.1 Provide the facility&#146;s written pollution
prevention policy statement that indicates management&#146;s and
employees&#146; commitment to preventing pollution and waste at
the source.</b> </p>
<p>This is the facility&#146;s statement indicating a commitment
by management and employees to preventing pollution at the
source. </p>
<p><b>2.2 Provide a brief description of the facility&#146;s
operations. (If available, provide a process flow diagram)</b> </p>
<p>Describe what product(s) is made at the facility and what
processes are used to make the product(s). </p>
<p><b>2. 3 Use the following charts (2.4 - 2.9) to list the
facility&#146;s waste streams and determine the amount of waste
reduced through pollution prevention . (Make copies of charts if
necessary to list all types of waste)</b> </p>
<p>The following charts are designed to help establish that the
facility has met reduction goals required to qualify for the
Achievement Level and to receive a reduction in hazardous waste
trust fund and Toxic Release Inventory fees from the Georgia
Environmental Protection Division. Facilities must achieve 25
percent of overall reduction goals stated in its pollution
prevention plan.</p>
<p>Identify the waste streams that your facility generated and
production for the baseline year. (To qualify for the Achievement
Level the baseline year must be 1994 or earlier.)</p>
<ul>
    <li>Enter air emissions in pounds (2.4), wastewater/water use
        in gallons (2.5), hazardous waste in tons (2.6), and
        solid waste in tons (2.7). <b>Not all facilities generate
        waste in each category.</b> </li>
    <li>Production is the number or amount of finished products
        made at the facility. Please indicate production quantity
        or units.</li>
    <li>The Reduction Goals Summary Sheet (2.8) is used to total
        waste reductions and determine if enough waste has been
        eliminated to qualify for the Achievement Level.</li>
</ul>
<p>Specific instructions for each chart are detailed below.</p>
<p><b>For plants with annual regulatory reporting requirements
for air emissions, hazardous waste, and/or wastewater that
include a production indices,</b> please identify the appropriate
documents. P<sup>2</sup>AD will review the identified documents
at the Environmental Protection Division and plant may choose not
to fill out tables 2.4 - 2.7. However, the plant will still be
required to fill out Table 2.8, The Reduction Goals<b> </b>Summary
Sheet. </p>
<p><b>2.4 Air Emissions Worksheet</b> </p>
<p>Potential air emissions types include the following: </p>
<ul>
    <li>VOCs (Volatile Organic Compounds) - Plant may choose to
        identify specific VOCs or summarize all VOCs emitted into
        one number. </li>
    <li>HAPs (Hazardous Air Pollutants) - Again, plant may choose
        to identify specific HAPs or summarize all HAPs emitted
        into one number. </li>
    <li>Sulphur and Nitrogen Oxides, particulates if plant has a
        boiler or incinerator, etc. </li>
</ul>
<p>At top of table, enter baseline year (1994 or earlier). </p>
<p><i>Column 1 - </i>For each emission type, list the type of air
emission. </p>
<p><i>Column 2 - </i>For each emission type, list the source of
the emission. Example sources include stack emissions from boiler
or incinerator, paint booth emissions, vapor degreaser, solvent
cleaning, grinding dust, vapor emission from storage tank,
fugitive emissions. </p>
<p><i>Column 3 - </i>(A) Enter baseline year air emissions of
each type of air emission in pounds. </p>
<p><i>Column 4- </i>(B) Enter baseline year production in
specific units. Product quantities or dollar values are
preferred. Examples include automobiles, lineal feet of pipe,
number of employees, annual sales, gallons of cleaning chemicals.
Production numbers will be used to normalize waste reduction
percentages based on production levels. </p>
<p><i>Column 5 - </i>(C) Enter 1995 air emissions of each type of
air emission in pounds. </p>
<p><i>Column 6 - </i>(D) Enter 1995 production quantity in
specific units. Product quantities or dollar values are
preferred. </p>
<p><i>Column 7 - </i>(E) Calculate air emission reduction in
percent from baseline year to 1995 normalized for production
variations and enter the number in this cell. Substitute the
appropriate numbers in the following equation: </p>
<p><i>E = 1 - ((C/D)/(A/B))</i> = % air emissions reduction from
baseline year to 1995 </p>
<p><i>Column 8 - </i>Enter your long term waste reduction goal
for the specific emission category. </p>
<p>Follow directions above for columns 1 through 8 for each type
of air emission. Make copies of the form if there are more than
three categories. When complete, fill in the Air Summary row as
follows: </p>
<p><i>Column 1 - </i>No entry. </p>
<p><i>Column 2 - </i>Add baseline year emissions (A) from each
category of air emissions and enter total in this cell. </p>
<p><i>Column 3 - </i>Enter baseline year plant production. </p>
<p><i>Column 4 - </i>Add 1995 emissions (C) for each type of
emission and enter total in this cell. </p>
<p><i>Column 5 - </i>Enter 1995 plant production. </p>
<p><i>Column 6 -</i> Calculate total air emissions reductions in
percent from baseline year to 1995 normalized for production
variations and enter the number in this cell. Substitute the
appropriate numbers in the following equation: </p>
<p><i>J = 1 - ((H/I)/(F/G)) * 100 = </i>Total % emissions reduced
from baseline year to 1995 </p>
<p><i>Column 7 - </i>Enter your plant&#146;s long term reduction
goal for air emissions in % (From Entry Level plan or existing
company goals). </p>
<p><i>Column 8 - </i>Enter the percentage of the plant air
emissions reduction goal that has been achieved by the end of
1995. Use the following equation: </p>
<p><i>L = J/K * 100 = % of long term goal achieved</i> </p>
<p><b>2.5 Wastewater / Water Use Worksheet</b> </p>
<p>Example types of wastewater may include process vs.
non-process, potable water, water used in product, cooling water,
boiler feed water, city water, or it can be separated by specific
processes - i.e., plating rinsewater, quench water, etc.
Wastewater may include NPDES and POTW effluent in addition to
wastewater to a pretreatment plant at the facility. </p>
<p>At top of table, enter baseline year (1994 or earlier). </p>
<p><i>Column 1 - </i>For each type of water use, list the type of
water use / waste water. </p>
<p><i>Column 2 - </i>(A) Enter baseline year water use for each
type in gallons. </p>
<p><i>Column 3- </i>(B) Enter baseline year production in
specific units. Product quantities or dollar values are
preferred. Examples include automobiles, lineal feet of pipe,
number of employees, annual sales, gallons of cleaning chemicals.
Production numbers will be used to normalize waste reduction
percentages based on production levels. </p>
<p><i>Column 5 - </i>(C) Enter 1995 water use for each type of
use in gallons. </p>
<p><i>Column 6 - </i>(D) Enter 1995 production quantity in
specific units. Product quantities or dollar values are
preferred. </p>
<p><i>Column 7 - </i>(E) Calculate water use reduction in percent
from baseline year to 1995 normalized for production variations
and enter the number in this cell. Substitute the appropriate
numbers in the following equation: </p>
<p><i>E = 1 - ((C/D)/(A/B))</i> + 100 = % water use reduction
from baseline year to 1995 </p>
<p><i>Column 8 - </i>Enter your long term waste reduction goal
for each water use category. </p>
<p>Follow directions above for column 1 through 8 for each type
of water usage. Make copies of the form if there are more than
three categories. When complete, fill in the bottom row as
follows: </p>
<p><i>Column 1 - </i>Add baseline year water use (A) from each
category of water use and enter total in this cell. </p>
<p><i>Column 2 - </i>Enter baseline year plant production. </p>
<p><i>Column 3 - </i>Add 1995 water use (C) for each type of
emission and enter total in this cell. </p>
<p><i>Column 5 - </i>Enter 1995 plant production. </p>
<p><i>Column 6 -</i> Calculate total water use reduction in
percent from baseline year to 1995 normalized for production
variations and enter the number in this cell. Substitute the
appropriate numbers in the following equation: </p>
<p><i>J = 1 - ((H/I)/(F/G)) * 100 = </i>Total % water use reduced
in 1995 based on baseline year. </p>
<p><i>Column 7 - </i>Enter your plant&#146;s long term reduction
goal for water use in % (From Entry Level plan or existing
company goals). </p>
<p><i>Column 8 - </i>Enter the percentage of the plant water use
reduction goal that has been achieved by the end of 1995. Use the
following equation: </p>
<p><i>L = J/K * 100 = % of long term goal achieved</i> </p>
<p>The plant shall decide which level of detail sufficiently
portrays their water usage. The plant numerical goals for water
use, hazardous waste, and solid waste may differ from air
emissions reduction goals. </p>
<p><b>2.6 Hazardous Waste Worksheet</b> </p>
<p>Examples of hazardous wastes include many solvents, acids and
bases, heavy metals and inorganics, ignitable wastes, ink sludges
containing chromium and lead, lead-acid batteries, pesticides,
reactive wastes, spent plating and cyanide wastes, and wood
preserving agents. A company may choose to identify the hazardous
waste by its EPA Hazardous Waste Number. </p>
<p>At top of table, enter baseline year (1994 or earlier). </p>
<p><i>Column 1 - </i>For each type of hazardous waste, list the
waste. </p>
<p><i>Column 2 - </i>For each type of hazardous waste, list the
source of the waste. Example sources may include parts washers,
adhesives, paint booth sludges, printing inks, fuel spills,
mixing tanks, etc. </p>
<p><i>Column 3 - </i>(A) Enter baseline year hazardous waste
generation for each type of hazardous waste in pounds or tons. </p>
<p><i>Column 4- </i>(B) Enter baseline year production in
specific units. Product quantities or dollar values are
preferred. Examples include automobiles, lineal feet of pipe,
number of employees, annual sales, gallons of cleaning chemicals.
Production numbers will be used to normalize waste reduction
percentages based on production levels. </p>
<p><i>Column 5 - </i>(C) Enter 1995 hazardous waste generation
for each type of hazardous waste in pounds or tons. </p>
<p><i>Column 6 - </i>(D) Enter 1995 production quantity in
specific units. Product quantities or dollar values are
preferred. </p>
<p><i>Column 7 - </i>(E) Calculate hazardous waste reduction in
percent from baseline year to 1995 normalized for production
variations and enter the number in this cell. Substitute the
appropriate numbers in the following equation: </p>
<p><i>E = 1 - ((C/D)/(A/B))</i> * 100 = % hazardous waste
reduction from baseline year to 1995 </p>
<p><i>Column 8 - </i>Enter your long term waste reduction goal
for the specific hazardous waste or hazardous waste category. </p>
<p>Follow directions above for column 1 through 8 for each type
of hazardous waste. Make copies of the form if there are more
than three categories. When complete, fill in the Hazardous Waste
Summary row as follows: </p>
<p><i>Column 1 - </i>No entry. </p>
<p><i>Column 2 - </i>Add baseline year hazardous waste generation
(A) from each category of hazardous waste and enter total in this
cell. </p>
<p><i>Column 3 - </i>Enter baseline year plant production. </p>
<p><i>Column 4 - </i>Add 1995 hazardous waste generation (C) for
each type of hazardous waste and enter total in this cell. </p>
<p><i>Column 5 - </i>Enter 1995 plant production. </p>
<p><i>Column 6 -</i> Calculate hazardous waste reductions in
percent from baseline year to 1995 normalized for production
variations and enter the number in this cell. Substitute the
appropriate numbers in the following equation: </p>
<p><i>J = 1 - ((H/I)/(F/G)) * 100 = </i>Total % hazardous waste
reduced from baseline year to 1995 </p>
<p><i>Column 7 - </i>Enter your plant&#146;s long term reduction
goal for hazardous waste in % (From Entry Level plan or existing
company goals). </p>
<p><i>Column 8 - </i>Enter the percentage of the plant hazardous
waste reduction goal that has been achieved by the end of 1995.
Use the following equation: </p>
<p><i>L = J/K * 100 = % of long term goal achieved</i> </p>
<p><b>2.7 Solid Waste Worksheet</b> </p>
<p>Example solid wastes include office wastes, cafeteria wastes,
cardboard, shrink wrap, metals, pallets, wood, papers, crating,
plastics, glass, packaging, etc. </p>
<p>At top of table, enter baseline year (1994 or earlier). </p>
<p><i>Column 1 - </i>For each type of solid waste, list the
waste. </p>
<p><i>Column 2 - </i>For each type of solid waste, list the
source of the waste. Example sources may include shipping &amp;
receiving, office, cafeteria, grinding, cutting, out of
specification product, etc. </p>
<p><i>Column 3 - </i>(A) Enter baseline year solid waste
generation for each type of solid waste in pounds. </p>
<p><i>Column 4- </i>(B) Enter baseline year production in
specific units. Product quantities or dollar values are
preferred. Examples include automobiles, lineal feet of pipe,
number of employees, annual sales, gallons of cleaning chemicals.
Production numbers will be used to normalize waste reduction
percentages based on production levels. </p>
<p><i>Column 5 -</i> (C) Enter 1995 solid waste generation for
each type of hazardous waste in pounds. </p>
<p><i>Column 6 - </i>(D) Enter 1995 production quantity in
specific units. Product quantities or dollar values are
preferred. </p>
<p><i>Column 7 - </i>(E) Calculate solid waste reduction in
percent from baseline year to 1995 normalized for production
variations and enter the number in this cell. Substitute the
appropriate numbers in the following equation: </p>
<p><i>E = 1 - ((C/D)/(A/B))</i> * 100 = % solid waste reduction
from baseline year to 1995 </p>
<p><i>Column 8 - </i>Enter your long term waste reduction goal
for the specific solid waste or solid waste category. </p>
<p>Follow directions above for column 1 through 8 for each type
of solid waste. Make copies of the form if there are more than
three categories. When complete, Fill in the Solid Waste Summary
row as follows: </p>
<p><i>Column 1 - </i>No entry. </p>
<p><i>Column 2 - </i>Add baseline year solid waste generation (A)
from each category of solid waste and enter total in this cell. </p>
<p><i>Column 3 - </i>Enter baseline year plant production. </p>
<p><i>Column 4 - </i>Add 1995 solid waste generation (C) for each
type of hazardous waste and enter total in this cell. </p>
<p><i>Column 5 - </i>Enter 1995 plant production. </p>
<p><i>Column 6 -</i> Calculate solid waste reductions in percent
from baseline year to 1995 normalized for production variations
and enter the number in this cell. Substitute the appropriate
numbers in the following equation: </p>
<p><i>J = 1 - ((H/I)/(F/G)) * 100 = </i>Total % solid waste
reduced from baseline year to 1995 </p>
<p><i>Column 7 - </i>Enter your plant&#146;s long term reduction
goal for solid waste in % (From Entry Level plan or existing
company goals). </p>
<p><i>Column 8 - </i>Enter the percentage of the plant solid
waste reduction goal that has been achieved by the end of 1995.
Use the following equation: </p>
<p><i>L = J/K * 100 = % of long term goal achieved</i> </p>
<p><b>2.8 Reduction Goal Summary Sheet</b> </p>
<p><i>Column 1 - </i>Contains waste type - no entry necessary. </p>
<p><i>Column 2 - </i>Enter plant long term reduction goals in %
for each category of waste. These numbers should match up with
item (K) in the summary row of each worksheet. For totals line,
use the following equation to set long term overall reduction
goal: </p>
<p><i>E1 = .25 * A1 + .25 * B1 + .25 * C1 + .25 * D1 = Long term
reduction goal*</i> </p>
<p><i>Column 3 - </i>Enter plant % of long term goal achieved for
each category. These numbers should match up with item (L) in the
summary row of each worksheet. For totals line, use the following
equation to calculate overall plant percentage of long term goal
achieved: </p>
<p><i>E2 = .25 * A2 + .25 * B2 + .25 * C2 + .25 * D2 =Percentage
of long term goal achieved*</i> </p>
<p>The summary sheet identifies the necessary data to determine
if the plant has met the quantitative requirements of the
achievement level award. </p>
<p><b>(*NOTE: If there are only three categories of waste,
multiply by .33 each. If there are only 2 categories multiply by
.5 each.)</b> </p>
<p><b>2.9 Detail any cost savings achieved through the pollution
prevention program.</b> </p>
<p>Show any savings realized through the pollution prevention
program. Savings may include, but are not limited to, reduced
disposal costs, reduced fees, reduced overhead, reduced purchases
of raw materials and reduced liability costs. Calculate expected
pay back period or net present value of project. </p>
<hr>
<h3><b>Section 3.0 - Employee Participation</b> </h3>
<p><b>3.1 Describe the makeup of the facility&#146;s pollution
prevention team and how it functions.</b> </p>
<p>List positions or areas of responsibility represented on the
team, how often it meets and to whom does the team report. </p>
<p><b>3.2 Describe how employees of the facility are kept
informed about the pollution prevention program.</b> </p>
<p>Indicate by what means employees are told about the pollution
prevention program and updated on its progress. </p>
<p><b>3.3 Describe how employees are encouraged to participate in
the pollution prevention program.</b> </p>
<p>List any motivational efforts or incentives offered to
employees for contributing to the program. </p>
<hr>
<h3><b>Section 4.0 - Management Commitment</b> </h3>
<p><b>4.1 Describe how pollution prevention is incorporated into
the facility&#146;s business plan or plan of operation.</b> </p>
<p>Detail references to the pollution prevention plan in the
company&#146;s or facility&#146;s business plans, operations
plans or annual reports. </p>
<hr>
<h3><b>Section 5.0 - Outreach</b> </h3>
<p><b>5.1 Describe how the facility has informed the surrounding
community of its pollution prevention program.</b> </p>
<p>Indicate by what means the community surrounding the facility
was notified of the facility&#146;s pollution prevention program. </p>
<p><b>5.2 Describe how the facility has encouraged pollution
prevention in the surrounding community.</b> </p>
<p>List any environmental outreach or community involvement
programs the facility has conducted with the community. </p>
<hr>
<h3><b>Section 6.0 - Fee Reductions</b> </h3>
<p>To receive any reductions in fees the following statement must
be signed by the highest ranking company official at the
facility. </p>
<p><b>6.1 The undersigned hereby agrees that any reduction or
waiver of the fees imposed by the Georgia Environmental
Protection Division must be used toward the cost of implementing
its pollution prevention programs and activities. The application
of said fees will be documented in accordance with accepted
accounting principles.</b> </p>
<p>______________________________ Date_________ </p>
<p><b>6.2 If the facility received a reduction in fees in the
previous year, describe how the saved funds were spent on the
company&#146;s pollution prevention program.</b> </p>
<p>List the dollar amounts saved from the fee reductions and how
the funds were applied to the facility&#146;s pollution
prevention program. </p>
<hr>
<h3><b>Section 7.0 - Signature and Certification</b> </h3>
<p><b>The highest ranking manager at the facility, and a
registered Professional Engineer must sign the following
statement:</b> </p>
<p>I certify that the information contained in this document is
true, accurate and complete. </p>
<p>Company Officer:______________________________ </p>
<p>Title:______________________________ </p>
<p>Date:______________________________ </p>
<p>The Professional Engineer must be registered as a Professional
Engineer in the State of Georgia for the current calendar. </p>
<p>Professional Engineer:_________________________ </p>
<p>Date:______________________________ </p>
<hr>
