<title>Wood Finishers and Furniture Manufacturers Encouraged to Attend Teleconference and Workshop</title>
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/images/whttxtr1.jpg" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p>[ <a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/index.htm">Home</a> | <a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/news.htm">What's New</a> | <a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/toc.htm">TOC</a> | <a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/feedback.htm">Feedback</a> | <a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/search.htm">Search</a> ]</p>
<h2><img src="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/images/epd.gif" align=left hspace=0 width=100 height=100>Environmental Protection Division</h2>
<h3 align=left>GA EPD Right-To-Know Office - (404) 656-6905<br>
<strong>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE:</strong></h3>
<p align=left>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE	CONTACT: Anita Dorsey-Word<br>
(770) 362-4842<br>
<br>
<br>
Wood Finishers and Furniture Manufacturers Encouraged to Attend Teleconference and Workshop<br>
<br>
<br>
Atlanta, Georgia - A teleconference and workshop will be held September 18, 1996, at the Environmental Protection Division 
Training Center in Atlanta. This day long teleconference and workshop will help wood furniture manufacturers and cabinet 
makers understand what they must do to satisfy new requirements under the Clean Air Act. Most furniture manufacturers, 
regardless of size, are affected by these new requirements and are encouraged to attend.<br>
<br>
The speakers will be from various industry and state programs. Some questions they will answer during the program include: 
Who is affected? Who must control emissions? Who must keep records and reports? How can I identify pollution prevention 
techniques that will save money and reduce waste such as selecting the best spray paint gun and using good coating 
techniques?<br>
<br>
The program is free and sponsored locally by the Environmental Protection Division/Small Business Assistance Program, 
Pollution Prevention Assistance Division, Georgia Institute of Technology, and the Southeastern Environmental Research 
Alliance. Other participants include the American Furniture Manufacturing Association, the Kitchen Cabinet Manufacturing 
Association, the Business and Industrial Furniture Manufacturing Association, the National Painting and Coating Association, 
the DeVilbiss Company, Sherwin-Williams Company, and the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA). <br>
<br>
Georgia Tech will issue 0.8 Continuing Education Credits for full day attendees.<br>
<br>
For more information and to register for the teleconference and workshop contact: <br>
Ricky Whitted at (404)651-5120.<br>
<br>
Teleconference and Workshop Site:<br>
Environmental Protection Division Training Center <br>
4244 International Parkway, Suite 120, Atlanta, Georgia 30354<br>
</p>
